<!DOCTYPE html>
<!--[if lt IE 7]>      <html class="no-js lt-ie9 lt-ie8 lt-ie7"> <![endif]-->
<!--[if IE 7]>         <html class="no-js lt-ie9 lt-ie8"> <![endif]-->
<!--[if IE 8]>         <html class="no-js lt-ie9"> <![endif]-->
<!--[if gt IE 8]><!--> <html class="no-js" lang="en"> <!--<![endif]-->
<!-- @page_name = Church360º Design System / Case Study / -->
<!-- @page_description = A complete, production-ready design system built directly into the product codebase for a leading church management platform. -->
<!-- @import "/partials/headtag" -->
<body class="work-landing">
  <div class="scroll-on-page">
    <!-- @import "/partials/header.html" -->
    <section id="details" name="details" class="case-study-overview">
      <div class="wrapper">
        <h5><span>Case Study</span> Church360° Design System</h5>
        <h1>Building Consistency Across a Growing Ministry Platform</h1>
        <div class="overview">
          <h4>Overview</h4>
          <p>A complete, production-ready design system built directly into the product codebase for a leading church management platform.</p>
          <p><a href="#overview" class="scroll-on-page-link" >View Project</a></p>
        </div>
        <div class="my-role">
          <h4>My Role</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>UX Design</li>
            <li>UI Design</li>
            <li>Frontend Development</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section>
      <div class="wrapper">
        <img class="case-study-hero-image" src="/img/360-design-darklightmode.png" alt="Laptop showing Church360° in light and dark mode">
      </div>
    </section>
    <section id="overview" name="overview">
      <div class="wrapper">
        <h3>A Living Design System</h3>
        <div class="design-system-overview">
          <div>
            
            <p><strong>The Challenge:</strong> Church360° was shifting from a traditional licensing model to a pay-per-module subscription model while merging three separate products into one unified platform.</p>
              <p>This major transformation created a critical need for consistency, scalability, and a cohesive user experience across a significantly larger and more complex application.</p>
              <p>I led the creation of a comprehensive design system embedded directly in the product codebase to support this evolution and ensure long-term maintainability.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="card-components">
            <div><span>60+</span>Components</div>
            <div><span>200+</span>Icon</div>
            <div><span>∞</span>Tokens</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
      </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- EXPERIENCE PRINCIPLES -->
<section class="princples">
  <div class="wrapper">
  <h3>Experience Principles</h3>
  
  <div class="principles-grid">
      
      <!-- Principle 1 -->
      <div class="principle">
          <div class="principle-icon">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 01-3-3V9a3 3 0 01-3-3V4a3 3 0 013-3h2" />
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 013-3V9a3 3 0 013-3V4a3 3 0 01-3-3H4" />
              </svg>
          </div>
          <div>
              <h4>Empathetic and Human</h4>
              <p>Ministry management should be human because we are human. Church360° recognizes problems and uses data to ensure the app reduces stress, is easy-to-use, and increases productivity.</p>
          </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Principle 2 -->
      <div class="principle">
        <div class="principle-icon">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"  fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M4 6h16M4 12h16M4 18h7" />
              </svg>
          </div>
          <div>
              <h4>Consistent and Simplistic</h4>
              <p>Nothing should distract from the Church’s mission. Across all platforms Church360° is familiar, consistent, accessible, delightful, and easy to navigate.</p>
          </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Principle 3 -->
      <div class="principle">
        <div class="principle-icon">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"  fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 12a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z" />
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M2.458 12C3.732 7.943 7.523 5 12 5 16.477 5 20.268 7.943 21.542 12 20.268 16.057 16.477 19 12 19 7.523 19 3.732 16.057 2.458 12z" />
              </svg>
          </div>
          <div>
              <h4>Accessible and Intuitive</h4>
              <p>The Church includes all people. Church360° is inclusive for special needs, communicates clearly, and honestly. Anyone, no matter their technological background, is able to easily use the app.</p>
          </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Principle 4 -->
      <div class="principle">
        <div class="principle-icon">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z" />
              </svg>
          </div>
          <div>
              <h4>Safe and Secure</h4>
              <p>Keeping the church’s data secure is our number one priority. The Church members can keep their focus on Jesus, instead of worrying about their data.</p>
          </div>
      </div>

  </div>
</div>
</section>
    <section>
      <div class="wrapper">
          
        <div class="work-content-full">
            <h3>Process</h3>
            <p>A collaborative, user-centered approach combining strategy, research, iteration, and tight developer partnership.</p>
            <div class="process-step">
              <div class="title">
                  <div>PHASE 01</div>
                  <h3>Discovery &amp; Planning</h3>
              </div>
              <div class="list">
                  <ul>
                      <li><span>→</span><div><strong>Design Roadmap</strong> — Created a comprehensive phased plan for the platform unification.</div></li>
                      <li><span>→</span><div><strong>UI Audit</strong> — Thorough audit across three legacy products to identify inconsistencies.</div></li>
                      <li><span>→</span><div><strong>User Stories</strong> — Developed detailed user stories with church staff personas to guide prioritization.</div></li>
                  </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="process-step">
              <div class="title">
                  <div>PHASE 02</div>
                  <h3>Foundation</h3>
              </div>
              <div class="list">
                  <ul>
                      <li><span>→</span><div><strong>Design Principles</strong> — Defined core principles focused on empathy, consistency, accessibility, and security.</div></li>
                      <li><span>→</span><div><strong>Inspiration & Benchmarking</strong> — Researched modern design systems and ministry-focused tools.</div></li>
                      <li><span>→</span><div><strong>Design System Foundation</strong> — Built design tokens, typography, colors, and custom icon library (200+ icons).</div></li>
                  </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="process-step">
              <div class="title">
                  <div>PHASE 03</div>
                  <h3>Design & Implementation</h3>
              </div>
              <div class="list">
                  <ul>
                      <li><span>→</span><div><strong>Component Library</strong> — Developed 60+ reusable, accessible components directly in the codebase.</div></li>
                      <li><span>→</span><div><strong>Design Critique Meetings</strong> — Weekly collaborative sessions with developers and stakeholders.</div></li>
                  </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="process-step">
              <div class="title">
                  <div>PHASE 04</div>
                  <h3>Testing &amp; Validation</h3>
              </div>
              <div class="list">
                  <ul>
                      <li><span>→</span><div><strong>Usability Testing</strong> — Card sorting for navigation, user flow testing, and concept validation with real church staff.</div></li>
                      <li><span>→</span><div><strong>Accessibility Testing</strong> — Performed extensive accessibility testing and ensured full WCAG 2.1 AA compliance across the entire design system.</div></li>
                  </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="wrapper">
          <div class="browser-left">
            <figure class="full left zoom-effect">
              <div class="aspectRatioPlaceholder" >
                  <div class="aspect-ratio-fill" style="padding-bottom: 60.875%;"></div>
                  <img class="img" data-width="1600" data-height="1200" src="/img/360-icons.png" alt="Sample of icons from the Church360° custom icon library">
              </div>
            </figure>
        </div>
        <div class="work-content">
            <h3>Custom Icon Library</h3>
            <p>Over 200 meticulously crafted icons in Stroke 2, Stroke 3, and Bold weights.</p>
        </div>
        
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- DESIGN TOKENS -->
<section>
  <div class="wrapper">
    <div class="work-content">
  <h3>Design Tokens</h3>
  <div>
      <p>I established a robust, scalable foundation using design tokens for colors, typography, spacing, and shadows. This ensured consistency across the entire platform and made it easy for both designers and developers to maintain visual harmony.</p>
  </div>
</div>
  <div class="browser-right">
    <figure class="full right zoom-effect">
      <div class="aspectRatioPlaceholder" >
          <div class="aspect-ratio-fill" style="padding-bottom: 60.875%;"></div>
          <img class="img" data-width="1600" data-height="1200" src="/img/360-color.png" alt="Sample of colors from the Church360° design system, showing primary, secondary, and neutral color palettes">
      </div>
    </figure>
  </div>
</div>
</section>
<!-- CONCLUSION -->
<section>
  <div class="wrapper">
    <div class="conclusion">
    <div class="conclusion-icon">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
    </svg>
    </div>
  <h2>Conclusion</h2>
  <div>
      <p>By creating a comprehensive design system embedded directly in the product codebase, we successfully unified three products into one cohesive platform. The result was not only visual and functional consistency but also dramatically improved development velocity and user experience.</p>
      <p><strong>🎉 100% component adoption across the platform marked this as a significant milestone in Church360°’s evolution.</strong></p>
  </div>
</div>
</div>
</section>
    
<section>
  <div class="wrapper">
    <a href="/case-studies/" class="btn">Back to Case Studies</a>   
  </div>
</section>
   
